    "title": {
      "rendered": "A Sneak Peek at Who Is Taking the 2018 Global Trends in Giving Survey"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p>Inspiring people to take online surveys is tough! We are grateful to the 3,573 people who have taken the <a href=\"https://www.funraise.org/giving-report\"><strong>2018 Global Trends In Giving Survey</strong></a> thus far. This year we are getting more participants from outside of the United States, but we definitely need more diversity in our survey respondents for the data to truly reflect the global donor community. The survey is available in five languages\u00a0\u2013 <strong>\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651\u0629</strong>, <strong>English</strong>, <strong>espa\u00f1ol</strong>, <strong>fran\u00e7ais</strong>, and <strong>portugu\u00eas</strong>\u00a0\u2013 to reach a global audience. Anything you can do to help spread the word about the survey to your corner of the world is greatly appreciated. The 2018 Global Trends in Giving Report will be released September 17, 2018 and is a sister report to the <a href=\"https://funraise.org/techreport-past-reports\"><strong>2018 Global NGO Technology Report</strong></a>.</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Gender</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>63.6% are female. 35.8% are male. 0.6% are non-binary.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://funraise.org/techreport-past-reports\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-22338 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Gender.jpg?resize=600%2C401\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Gender.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Gender.jpg?resize=300%2C201&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Generation</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3% are Gen Z. 33.5% are Millennials. 34.9% are Gen X.<br />\n25.4% are Baby Boomers. 3.2% are Matures.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22345\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Generation-2-1.jpg?resize=600%2C372\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Generation-2-1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Generation-2-1.jpg?resize=300%2C186&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Political Ideology</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Very liberal 24.8%. Somewhat liberal 29.2%. Moderate 32.1%.<br />\nSomewhat conservative 10.5%. Very conservative 3.4%.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22343\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Ideology.jpg?resize=600%2C412\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"412\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Ideology.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Ideology.jpg?resize=300%2C206&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Religion</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Buddhist 6%. Christian 36.7%. Hindu 1.8%. Jewish 14.7%.<br />\nMuslim 6.6%. Sikh 0.3%. Nonreligious 28.8%.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22347\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Religion.jpg?resize=600%2C382\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Religion.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Religion.jpg?resize=300%2C191&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Race (U.S. Only)</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Asian/Pacific Islander 2%. Black/African American 5.6%. Hispanic/Latino 4.6%.<br />\nNative American 0%.\u00a0White/Caucasian 83.3%. </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22349\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Race.jpg?resize=600%2C473\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"473\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Race.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Race.jpg?resize=300%2C237&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Top 10 Countries</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>United States 24.5%. Singapore 14%. Israel 13.3%. Canada 6%. Argentina 5.1%.<br />\nUnited Kingdom 4.9%.\u00a0Spain 3.7%. South Africa 3%. Australia 2.9%. Bangladesh 2.1%.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22350\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Countries.jpg?resize=600%2C416\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Countries.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Countries.jpg?resize=300%2C208&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">2018 Global NGO Technology Report</h2>\n<p>Published in \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651\u0629, English, fran\u00e7ais, portugu\u00eas y espa\u00f1ol, the <strong><a href=\"https://funraise.org/techreport-past-reports\">2018 Global NGO Technology Report</a></strong>\u00a0is based on the survey results of 5,352 NGOs from 164 countries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://funraise.org/techreport-past-reports\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-22066 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=600%2C315\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
